dct_description_sm: Printed with vegetation. Prepared under the direction of the Chief of Engineers by the Army Map Service (GE), Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army , [planimetry and contours] by U. S. Geological Survey. Variant title: Indiana 1:25,000. Filing title: Lewis Creek, Indiana : Shelby County. Standard map series designation: AMS (Series) V851 Sheet 3862 IV NE. Type C--AMS 1. "A.M.S. Series V851" "Transverse Mercator projection." Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Shows roads, railroads, boundaries, buildings, cemeteries, and natural features. "Contour interval 10 feet." Marginal maps: Index to boundaries.--Index to adjoining sheets. "Planimetry by stereophotogrammetric (multiplex) methods by the U. S. Geological Survey 1946. Contours by plane-table methods by the U. S. Geological Survey 1946-1947. Horizontal and vertical control by USGS and USC&GS. Aerial photography September 1941. Public Land Survey lines are based on the Second Principal Meridian and Base Line." "N3922.5-W8545/7.5." "Type C (AMS 1), 1947." "7-48."
Imprint: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army, 1948.
Dimensions: 56 x 45 cm or smaller; Scale: 1:25,000
dct_creator_sm: United States. Army Map Service; Geological Survey (U.S.)
